### IDP Workflow Demo
### Base URL for local development
@baseUrl = http://localhost:7071/api
# @baseUrl = https://idp-workbench.azurewebsites.net/api

### Authentication
### Get your Host Key from: Azure Portal → Function App → App Keys
### Or run: az functionapp keys list --name idp-workbench --resource-group idpworkbench --query "masterKey" -o tsv
@hostKey = O4M4_JY9de14s5Oc7uLpcHSHVbs2X_we98p8psYIv7VgAzFuP-pVNw==

### ========================================================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### ========================================================================

### Health check (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health?code={{hostKey}}

### ========================================================================
### START WORKFLOW
### ========================================================================

### 1. Start IDP workflow - HOME LOAN document
### The instanceId will be automatically captured from response
# @name startWorkflow
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/start?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "pdf_path": "./sample_documents/home_loan_zava.pdf",
    "domain_id": "home_loan"
}

### 2. Start IDP workflow - INSURANCE CLAIMS document
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/start?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "pdf_path": "/home/ssattiraju/projects/experiments/MAFAzFunc/sample_documents/insurance_claims_zava.pdf",
    "domain_id": "insurance_claims"
}

### 3. Start IDP workflow - SMALL BUSINESS LENDING document
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/start?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "pdf_path": "./sample_documents/small_business_lending_zava.pdf",
    "domain_id": "small_business_lending"
}

### ========================================================================
### SIGNALR CONNECTION (For Real-Time Updates)
### ========================================================================
### Note: SignalR negotiation is typically done from frontend JavaScript
### Use the IDP Workflow Monitor frontend app for real-time updates

### Negotiate SignalR connection (returns connection info)
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/negotiate?code={{hostKey}}

### Subscribe to workflow updates (join SignalR group)
### Automatically uses instanceId from the workflow start response
@instanceId = {{startWorkflow.response.body.$.instanceId}}
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/subscribe/{{instanceId}}?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Unsubscribe from workflow updates (leave SignalR group)
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/unsubscribe/{{instanceId}}?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ========================================================================
### HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP (HITL) REVIEW
### ========================================================================
### Use these after receiving a "hitlWaiting" event via SignalR
### The event will contain field comparisons with Azure and DSPy values

### Submit HITL Review - APPROVE with field selections
### Use this when you want to approve and select specific field values
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/hitl/review/{{instanceId}}?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "approved": true,
    "feedback": "All fields reviewed and approved",
    "reviewer": "john.doe@example.com",
    "field_selections": [
        {
            "field_name": "downPaymentAmount",
            "selected_source": "azure",
            "selected_value": "$50,000",
            "azure_value": "$50,000",
            "dspy_value": "$45,000",
            "notes": "Azure value more accurate"
        },
        {
            "field_name": "appraisedValue",
            "selected_source": "dspy",
            "selected_value": "$500,000",
            "azure_value": "$500,000",
            "dspy_value": "$500,000",
            "notes": "Both values match"
        }
    ],
    "accepted_values": {
        "downPaymentAmount": "$50,000",
        "appraisedValue": "$500,000"
    },
    "default_source": "azure"
}

### Submit HITL Review - APPROVE (simple approval, use comparison values)
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/hitl/review/{{instanceId}}?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "approved": true,
    "feedback": "Approved after review",
    "reviewer": "jane.smith@example.com",
    "field_selections": [],
    "accepted_values": {},
    "default_source": "comparison"
}

### Submit HITL Review - REJECT with feedback
POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/hitl/review/{{instanceId}}?code={{hostKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "approved": false,
    "feedback": "Too many discrepancies. Please reprocess the document.",
    "reviewer": "admin@example.com",
    "field_selections": [],
    "accepted_values": {}
}

### ========================================================================
### EXAMPLE WORKFLOW
### ========================================================================

### STEP 1: Start a workflow
# POST {{baseUrl}}/idp/start
# Copy the instanceId from response

### STEP 2: Open IDP Workflow Monitor frontend
# http://localhost:3000 (or your frontend URL)
# - Click "Connect to SignalR"
# - Enter the instanceId
# - Click "Subscribe"
# - Watch real-time updates as the workflow progresses

### STEP 3: When you receive "hitlWaiting" event:
# The event will contain:
# - fieldsForReview: List of field names needing review
# - fieldComparisons: Array with Azure and DSPy values for each field
#   Example:
#   {
#     "fieldName": "loanAmount",
#     "azureValue": "$250,000",
#     "dspyValue": "$250000",
#     "match": false,
#     "needsReview": true
#   }
# - reviewUrl: The endpoint to POST your review

### STEP 4: Submit your review using one of the HITL endpoints above
# - Select which value to use (Azure or DSPy) for each field
# - Provide feedback
# - Approve or reject

### STEP 5: Watch the workflow continue
# - Reasoning step will run
# - reasoningChunk events will stream results
# - workflowCompleted event will have final results

### ========================================================================
### TESTING DIFFERENT SCENARIOS
### ========================================================================

### Scenario 1: Test with matching fields (no HITL needed)
### If Azure and DSPy extractions match perfectly, workflow skips HITL

### Scenario 2: Test with mismatches (HITL required)
### When extractions differ, workflow pauses for human review

### Scenario 3: Test timeout behavior
### Start workflow, wait for HITL, don't respond within timeout period

### Scenario 4: Test rejection workflow
### Approve with "approved": false to see rejection handling
